WEBVTT

00:00.034 --> 00:04.640
Well, I'm gonna take the next few moments and just finish a message I started last week.

00:07.744 --> 00:10.768
There's nothing more important than hearing the voice of God.

00:13.011 --> 00:21.303
Because that is where direction, that's where faith, that's where so many things happen in our life.

00:22.624 --> 00:29.874
And I would suggest to you as we said last time that it's our ability to hear what God is speaking to us in a moment

00:30.370 --> 00:36.506
that empowers us in that moment and really can release God's power into the lives of other people.

00:37.849 --> 00:40.476
Granted, God speaks primarily through His Word.

00:40.536 --> 00:42.601
So I'm not in any way denying that.

00:42.621 --> 00:47.634
I think everybody understands that I'm a believer in the Word of God speaking to us.

00:48.738 --> 00:49.860
And yet I also know this.

00:49.980 --> 01:05.463
I know that you and I need to learn to cultivate a sensitivity, not only to the presence of the Lord, but to the voice of the Lord, because through Him speaking to us, it positions us to minister to other people.

01:06.625 --> 01:15.698
It also positions us to walk out our faith in a practical and a powerful way where other people can see

01:15.810 --> 01:20.276
evidence of his supernatural hand on our life and know that there is a God.

01:21.598 --> 01:24.402
So last time we talked about, are you listening?

01:24.442 --> 01:27.427
We have to be listening for the voice of the Lord.

01:27.827 --> 01:30.251
But tonight I want to talk to you about how to hear God's voice.

01:30.511 --> 01:34.917
And we're going to look at 1 Samuel chapter three and beginning in verse one.

01:35.778 --> 01:38.823
The boy Samuel ministered before the Lord under Eli.

01:38.923 --> 01:40.004
Eli was the high priest.

01:41.406 --> 01:43.890
Samuel, you remember, had been given by

01:43.970 --> 01:47.775
his mother to the Lord because she received him from the Lord.

01:48.096 --> 01:58.690
She brought him to Eli because she and her husband were part of the tribe of Levi, which is the priestly tribe in Israel.

01:59.651 --> 02:00.613
So Eli's there.

02:00.653 --> 02:02.696
He's not his father, his biological father.

02:02.756 --> 02:06.801
Eli has to biological sons who are thoroughly wicked.

02:08.523 --> 02:10.386
And the Lord places

02:11.170 --> 02:15.796
the responsibility for their behavior in part at Eli's feet.

02:15.817 --> 02:23.928
Samuel, on the other hand, is there in the presence of the Lord, even though Eli is not really walking in the presence.

02:23.988 --> 02:28.554
In those days, the word of the Lord was rare, and there were not many visions.

02:28.574 --> 02:34.383
One night, Eli, whose eyes were becoming so weak that he could barely see, was lying down in his usual place.

02:34.443 --> 02:39.730
So remember, not many visions, and Eli can't see his physical

02:39.874 --> 02:43.720
condition is indicative of his spiritual condition.

02:45.022 --> 02:52.033
The lamp of God had not yet gone out, and Samuel was lying down in the temple of the Lord where the ark of God was.

02:53.316 --> 03:04.654
Then the Lord called Samuel, Samuel answered, here I am, and he ran to Eli and said, here I am, you called me, but Eli said, I did not call, go back and lie down, so he went and lay down.

03:04.694 --> 03:07.378
Again, the Lord called Samuel,

03:07.490 --> 03:15.160
And Samuel got up and went to Eli and said, here I am, you called me, my son Eli said, I did not call, go back and lie down.

03:15.901 --> 03:22.430
Now Samuel did not yet know the Lord, the word of the Lord had not yet been revealed to him.

03:23.191 --> 03:30.982
I think this is a very interesting statement in this, he can hear the word of the Lord, but he doesn't know it's the word of the Lord.

03:32.363 --> 03:37.330
I think that describes a lot of believers, the Lord is speaking, they just don't recognize he's speaking.

03:38.210 --> 03:52.274
because he's speaking through a friend, because he's gripping their heart with something, and they haven't yet learned when it is the word of the Lord, when it's the Lord speaking, when it's their own voice speaking.

03:53.316 --> 03:59.026
And so a part of growing in Christ is discerning how God speaks to us

03:59.138 --> 04:04.686
And let me just say this, let me caution everybody because invariably, if you ask somebody, how do you know when it's God speaking?

04:04.967 --> 04:09.994
Everybody kind of has their matrix for how that works in their life.

04:10.395 --> 04:16.744
And yet I caution you because God is never gonna let any of us come to the place where we think we've got him figured out.

04:17.866 --> 04:24.816
About the time you think you got it figured out, God's gonna say, okay, that lesson's done, let's move on and I'm gonna teach you another way I speak.

04:26.118 --> 04:29.042
Because he wants us to grow in our ability to hear him.

04:29.698 --> 04:34.384
So here Samuel, he's just now getting started in the Lord called Samuel a third time.

04:34.925 --> 04:38.229
And Samuel got up, went to Eli and said, here I am, you called me.

04:39.131 --> 04:42.375
Then Eli realized that the Lord was calling the boy.

04:43.276 --> 04:45.579
So Eli told Samuel, go and lie down.

04:45.980 --> 04:51.707
And if he calls you, say, speak, Lord, for your servant is listening.

04:53.109 --> 04:56.594
So Samuel went and laid down in his place.

04:57.282 --> 05:08.125
And the Lord came and stood there calling us at other times, Samuel, Samuel, then Samuel said, speak for your servant is listening.

05:08.867 --> 05:12.415
What I want to do is I want to give you seven things that can help us hear from God.

05:12.635 --> 05:13.677
How do we hear from God?

05:13.697 --> 05:15.160
Number one, repentance.

05:16.223 --> 05:17.746
Repentance means

05:17.922 --> 05:19.905
changing the way we think.

05:20.025 --> 05:24.751
It's not so much saying you're sorry, though that could be a part of it, saying you're sorry to God.

05:25.152 --> 05:27.055
It's changing the way you thought.

05:27.115 --> 05:33.323
You thought about something this way, but now you realize no God thinks about it this way.

05:33.724 --> 05:38.030
And so you change your thinking and you change your life.

05:39.331 --> 05:42.476
When we are repenting, we're confessing our sin to God.

05:42.836 --> 05:47.122
So one of the things that keeps people from hearing from God is un-

05:47.330 --> 05:49.618
can fast sand in their life.

05:51.842 --> 05:53.665
So they know they're not right with God.

05:53.986 --> 05:55.889
They know they've allowed things in their life.

05:56.249 --> 05:57.572
And they're not hearing from God.

05:57.952 --> 06:00.136
And what a lot of people do is they say, well, you know what?

06:00.156 --> 06:06.146
I'm just, I'm not as sensitive as someone so or God doesn't talk to me like he talks to so and so.

06:06.467 --> 06:07.969
Listen, that's not the issue at all.

06:08.310 --> 06:10.093
God speaks all the time.

06:10.374 --> 06:15.482
He talks to people and he wants to talk to everybody in this room, everybody watching online.

06:15.863 --> 06:17.746
He is a God who speaks.

06:17.890 --> 06:22.836
over 3,800 times in the Bible, it references the Lord speaking.

06:24.498 --> 06:28.403
And he speaks to all kinds of people in all kinds of circumstances.

06:28.703 --> 06:35.371
And if you're a Christian, you're his child, he wants to speak to you not once in a while, he wants to speak to you regularly.

06:36.272 --> 06:44.442
So if he's not speaking, the first thing you gotta ask yourself is, are there things in my life that are displeasing to the Lord?

06:45.584 --> 06:47.666
In Eli's situation, imagine this,

06:47.842 --> 06:50.065
The Lord is calling out to Samuel.

06:50.426 --> 06:53.110
Samuel can hear him, but Eli can't.

06:54.572 --> 07:03.825
And even when he knows it's the voice of the Lord, there's no sense in the text that Eli is hearing the voice, only Samuel's hearing it.

07:04.045 --> 07:09.473
And the question is, why can't the high priest hear God's voice?

07:09.493 --> 07:12.818
1 Samuel 2, 22.

07:13.346 --> 07:24.044
Now Eli, who was very old, heard about everything his sons were doing to all Israel, how they slept with the women who served at the entrance to the tent of meeting.

07:24.525 --> 07:29.814
In verse 29, we read this, why do you scorn God sent a prophet to ask him?

07:29.854 --> 07:33.881
Why do you scorn my sacrifice and offering that I prescribed to my dwelling?

07:33.921 --> 07:39.410
In other words, they were going and they were taking the best part of the offering rather than giving it to God.

07:40.610 --> 07:44.455
In verse 30, the Lord says, but now the Lord declares far be it for me.

07:44.836 --> 07:51.705
Those who honor me, I will honor, but those who despise me will be distinct.

07:54.529 --> 07:55.270
What's that saying?

07:55.671 --> 07:56.772
The word is to Eli.

07:57.153 --> 08:03.762
And what the prophet is saying is God is telling you you're not honoring him.

08:05.570 --> 08:14.984
And when you don't honor God with a life of purity, with a life of consecration, with a life of devotion, then you're not going to hear God's voice.

08:15.044 --> 08:16.707
That's the problem for Eli.

08:16.727 --> 08:31.890
1 Samuel 3.13, for I told him I would judge his family forever because of the sin he knew about, his sons made themselves contemptible, and he failed to restrain them.

08:34.882 --> 08:52.444
Parents, you and I have a responsibility to teach our children, to train them in the way they're to go, and to direct them, and there are times where you have, as long as they are under your care, under your roof, and you have an accountability to restrain them from evil.

08:55.809 --> 09:03.218
And in Eli's case, he doesn't do it, and the result is he's not honoring God, therefore God is

09:03.298 --> 09:07.285
not honoring him by speaking to him.

09:08.767 --> 09:15.178
It's not even that he can't hear God's voice in one sense it is because God is speaking to Samuel.

09:15.619 --> 09:18.263
Eli knows what it is, but can't hear it for himself.

09:18.584 --> 09:24.754
But God is not speaking to Eli because Eli has unconfessed sin in his life.

09:26.626 --> 09:35.897
And remember when we're talking about the toleration of sin in our life, we have to be very, very careful because the time to stop sin is when it first appears.

09:37.519 --> 09:41.543
Because most sin comes by way of fleshly desire.

09:41.864 --> 09:45.067
In other words, it comes out of our own humanity.

09:46.289 --> 09:54.098
But when sin is repeated, we've opened then at that point the door to the enemy, to the devil.

09:55.394 --> 09:59.458
And now it becomes demonically energized through our toleration of it.

09:59.699 --> 10:02.762
It becomes demonically energized in a person's life.

10:03.062 --> 10:12.613
And at that point, it becomes much more difficult to eradicate and impossible without repentance.

10:12.633 --> 10:17.158
If you have unrepentant sin in your life, you're not gonna hear the voice of the Lord.

10:17.458 --> 10:21.222
This is what David writes in Psalm 66 verse 18.

10:21.523 --> 10:24.626
If I had cherished sin in my heart, the Lord would not have listened.

10:25.922 --> 10:30.727
He's not only going to not listen, you're not going to hear him speak.

10:33.129 --> 10:49.465
My concern for a lot of people is that they have this idea, well, you know what, when it comes to repentance, I'm gonna go ahead and do this, and then I'll ask God to forgive me, and they're banking on the opportunity to repent, not realizing that repentance is a gift from God.

10:49.765 --> 10:54.770
It is not initiated by you, it is initiated by the Holy Spirit working in your heart.

10:57.314 --> 11:00.237
You and I on our own would never repent.

11:03.761 --> 11:08.525
The Holy Spirit is the one who works that in the life of the believer.

11:08.545 --> 11:17.675
And if he doesn't work that, if God does not give you the gift of repentance, you will not repent and you will die in your sin.

11:17.695 --> 11:19.817
Or you will be trapped in your sin.

11:20.838 --> 11:24.722
This is why it's really critical that you and I not only

11:24.802 --> 11:35.535
We start a Christian life with repentance, but we walk it out with a continued repentance that helps us maintain a close relationship with God.

11:37.698 --> 11:45.948
So in some ways, repentance is a lifestyle where we're constantly aligning ourselves with God's thinking.

11:47.249 --> 11:50.994
And the result is that when you and I repent, we'll hear God's voice.

11:52.354 --> 11:58.362
Because the prompting to repent tense is the fact that you are hearing his voice.

12:01.266 --> 12:04.391
If you have a desire to repent, it's because you're hearing his voice.

12:06.754 --> 12:12.402
A woman came up, I was standing after the album, and a woman came up, and she said, I need to repent.

12:14.946 --> 12:17.732
And I said, oh, and then we had this discussion.

12:17.812 --> 12:20.818
And I have leadership posts there who were able to help me to pray.

12:21.559 --> 12:27.832
And then she was from another, she was from the Joplin area.

12:28.373 --> 12:31.600
And fortunately, the Joplin pastor was there and I was able to connect.

12:31.620 --> 12:36.530
But that prompting in the time of the recording,

12:36.642 --> 12:39.345
for the album was the Lord speaking to her heart.

12:39.385 --> 12:43.550
So the very fact that you have this urge to repent is God speaking it.

12:43.570 --> 12:46.313
If you don't act on that, he is gonna become very silent.

12:47.635 --> 12:50.118
Number two, position yourself close to God.

12:51.700 --> 12:53.582
I love this in first Samuel chapter three.

12:53.942 --> 12:57.086
Samuel was lying down in the temple of the Lord where the Ark of God was.

12:57.406 --> 13:03.794
He is as close as he can possibly be to the Lord's presence.

13:05.410 --> 13:06.714
proximity matters.

13:08.820 --> 13:11.207
This is why church is so important.

13:11.227 --> 13:16.042
You just gotta decide what's gonna really be the value in your life.

13:16.182 --> 13:18.770
What is really going to be pleasurable to your soul?

13:20.866 --> 13:32.764
And if church becomes something you have to do instead of something you want to do, if church is an obligation to you instead of a benefit to you, then it's going to be hard for you to show up at church.

13:32.824 --> 13:42.599
But if church is a benefit, if you realize what God is doing in every single time, you're in His presence.

13:42.620 --> 13:44.242
Then you say, I want to be.

13:45.666 --> 13:50.895
In your house, the psalmist says, I love the habitation of your house, the place where your glory dwells.

13:52.958 --> 14:01.132
There's something about being in the presence of the Lord that changes us and transforms us as we go from glory to glory to glory.

14:01.393 --> 14:05.159
You can literally position yourself in the presence of God.

14:05.179 --> 14:05.740
Where's Eli?

14:05.941 --> 14:07.123
He's in his usual place.

14:07.944 --> 14:09.106
He's not even close.

14:10.530 --> 14:13.696
This is why I would suggest it's really important to be in church.

14:13.716 --> 14:15.039
I realize I'm preaching to the choir.

14:15.460 --> 14:18.065
You're here, so congratulations.

14:18.125 --> 14:28.044
You positioned yourself in the presence of the Lord, and that will have lasting impact on your life, your home, your family, your decisions, your job.

14:28.245 --> 14:32.914
You're hearing the voice of the Lord long beyond tonight itself.

14:35.458 --> 14:53.031
You're going to go out of here different than you came in Jesus' name because you honored God with the sacrifice of praise, because you honored God with the sacrifice of your time, because you honored God by saying, you're a priority in my life, and I'm telling you, heaven notices that.

14:55.897 --> 14:58.802
So if you want to hear the voice of God, be at church.

14:59.074 --> 15:00.236
Be at the prayer meeting.

15:00.596 --> 15:01.718
Be in a life group.

15:01.978 --> 15:03.680
Have your regular time with the Lord.

15:04.061 --> 15:07.946
Anytime there's an opportunity to get close to God, take it.

15:08.326 --> 15:09.888
Listen to worship music.

15:10.169 --> 15:18.400
Do the things that saturate your being with his presence and you will find yourself hearing his voice.

15:21.484 --> 15:24.127
Number three, serve in the house of God.

15:25.049 --> 15:25.549
I love this.

15:25.589 --> 15:26.210
Here's Samuel.

15:26.591 --> 15:29.074
The boy Samuel was serving God.

15:29.154 --> 15:30.736
under Eli's direction.

15:32.098 --> 15:34.522
Most scholars think he's about eight years old at this time.

15:36.265 --> 15:37.787
How much can an eight-year-old do?

15:38.928 --> 15:44.036
Not a lot, but they can do something.

15:44.056 --> 15:44.917
How much can you do?

15:44.957 --> 15:48.082
Too many people are aware of what they can't do rather than what they can do.

15:50.274 --> 15:54.019
And I just want to encourage you, there is something about serving.

15:54.079 --> 16:14.546
It's not just sitting in his presence, but it's serving in his presence that really does increasingly open us up because now what happens if I'm just sitting in his presence, then I'm becoming a reservoir and I'm just receiving and I'm not giving and ultimately that will lead to stagnation in the life of a believer.

16:16.002 --> 16:33.312
If all you are is, give me, give me, give me, give me, and you're not releasing what God has done in your life, if you're not acting on the things that he's showing you, telling them to others and serving others, putting the Word of God into practice, not just being a hearer of the Word, but a doer of the Word.

16:34.474 --> 16:36.818
When you start serving

16:37.186 --> 16:39.609
things happen relative to God's voice.

16:39.990 --> 16:42.774
The question is, are you serving in Go check?

16:43.434 --> 16:45.117
Have you gone through Go check?

16:45.137 --> 16:46.619
Are you serving on a dream team?

16:49.122 --> 16:51.145
Are you in a life group?

16:53.528 --> 16:58.154
Because I promise you this, you're going to hear the voice of God in that life group.

17:00.077 --> 17:00.818
Say, what do you mean?

17:01.058 --> 17:03.040
because you're gonna have heard the message.

17:03.340 --> 17:05.122
They're gonna be talking about the message.

17:05.622 --> 17:16.293
And when they start talking, somebody is gonna say something you either did not hear or had not thought about that's gonna touch your heart in a profound way.

17:16.693 --> 17:23.920
And that is the voice of God to you in that situation that you would not have had had you not been in that life group.

17:23.940 --> 17:25.461
It's a very interesting thing.

17:26.202 --> 17:30.226
Get around the people of God, serve the people of God, serve people.

17:31.906 --> 17:37.093
Number four, listen for God's voice.

17:37.113 --> 17:41.319
And when you sense his presence, respond.

17:42.621 --> 17:45.345
Smith Wigglesworth was a man greatly used of God.

17:45.385 --> 17:49.871
And on occasion he said this, I think this is a really profound concept.

17:49.931 --> 18:00.946
When I catch the first breath of the Spirit, I leave everything and everybody to be in his presence, listen to this, to hear

18:01.122 --> 18:02.223
What do you have to say to me?

18:04.506 --> 18:05.648
Here's what he understood.

18:06.128 --> 18:11.535
Sometimes you sense the presence of God, but that doesn't mean you just keep going.

18:11.595 --> 18:14.619
It means you stop and you say, God, what are you trying to say to me?

18:17.603 --> 18:27.555
My first encounter with this was I was in Panama with a missionary, and I told him I'd bring a team.

18:27.655 --> 18:29.778
I kind of negotiated the deal.

18:29.890 --> 18:33.294
This is a man who had done several 40-day fast.

18:33.615 --> 18:34.957
He'd raised people from the dead.

18:37.039 --> 18:46.472
And so when I meet people who or know of people who have that kind of powerful ministry, I want to learn from them.

18:46.492 --> 18:50.958
So I said, I'll bring a team down if you'll promise me a day of your time.

18:52.380 --> 18:53.801
So he agreed to that.

18:53.862 --> 18:57.266
So we're with him and he's come off a

18:57.666 --> 19:09.142
several days fast, I don't remember how many days, but we'd be talking and all of a sudden you could sense the presence of the Lord come into the room and he'd say, let's pray.

19:09.182 --> 19:14.429
And he was on his face on the floor crying out to God.

19:16.271 --> 19:18.054
And then he'd get up like nothing had happened.

19:19.936 --> 19:21.138
And he'd say, now where were we?

19:23.234 --> 19:26.539
And then we, I mean, and I watched him through my time.

19:26.659 --> 19:34.551
I was down there for a week and with him for more than just actually a day, but this was a common practice.

19:34.892 --> 19:39.338
And he said, whenever I sense God's presence, I stopped to listen to what God has to say.

19:42.062 --> 19:45.027
I'm just saying there's something to what Smith Wigglesworth is saying.

19:45.488 --> 19:47.090
And you and I, we can

19:47.266 --> 19:53.916
turn off, it's like we're turning a radio off if God's presence is there and we're not responding to His presence.

19:55.057 --> 19:56.800
That's the time you say, well, man, I have a job.

19:56.840 --> 19:58.061
I can't really do that.

19:59.263 --> 20:00.084
You'll figure it out.

20:01.446 --> 20:02.288
You will figure it out.

20:02.828 --> 20:04.491
Hey, I'm going to quickly use the restroom.

20:04.611 --> 20:07.114
I don't know how you're going to do it, but there's one idea.

20:07.155 --> 20:13.424
You may say, well, anyway, you figured out.

20:13.444 --> 20:15.186
The Lord will give you wisdom on that.

20:16.450 --> 20:21.597
What's so sad here is that Eli knew exactly what Samuel was experiencing.

20:23.940 --> 20:38.360
He knew what God's voice sounded like so he could tell Samuel how to respond to the voice of the Lord, but he wasn't near God's presence, so he wasn't listening for God's voice, so he didn't hear God's voice.

20:40.784 --> 20:45.330
Here's another thing, it's possible to come to a place in your life where

20:45.474 --> 20:47.116
You don't even care about God's voice.

20:49.138 --> 20:51.121
You don't want to find tragic in this story.

20:51.181 --> 21:04.436
One of the most tragic things is Eli knows God is speaking audibly, obviously, but he won't get up from where he is and walk to where God is.

21:05.758 --> 21:09.522
You know, you just, you have to prioritize the voice of the Lord.

21:12.002 --> 21:19.714
But Eli is, you know, you can get so far away from the Lord that you don't really care whether or not you hear the voice of the Lord.

21:19.894 --> 21:35.097
And if you're indifferent to the Lord speaking to you, that should be a warning sign, a blaring siren and red light saying, you are in grave spiritual danger.

21:36.919 --> 21:41.266
Number five, when God calls, respond eagerly.

21:42.754 --> 21:49.222
Instead of debating in your mind, and I think one of the things that trips people up is they're like, well, what if I'm wrong?

21:49.262 --> 21:50.384
What if it's not the voice of God?

21:51.065 --> 21:52.246
My question is what if it is?

21:55.571 --> 21:57.593
Let's quit talking about what if it's not, what if it is?

22:00.357 --> 22:07.506
And what happens is delay not only dulls the voice of the Spirit in our life,

22:09.026 --> 22:18.920
But I would suggest to you that when God tells you to do something in that moment, there is a grace and a power on it that dissipates as you delay.

22:21.684 --> 22:30.717
So that if God tells you to go pray for somebody, your greatest opportunity for impact in praying for them is immediately.

22:31.078 --> 22:33.842
The longer you wait, the more

22:34.114 --> 22:36.797
the presence and power of God dissipates.

22:37.117 --> 22:37.317
Why?

22:37.377 --> 22:40.380
Because what's functioning in your life is not faith but doubt.

22:42.882 --> 22:43.823
We should understand that.

22:43.883 --> 22:46.186
I mean, you're debating whether it's the voice of God.

22:46.206 --> 22:47.427
Well, I don't know whether that's really God.

22:47.707 --> 22:48.648
Do you realize what that is?

22:48.928 --> 22:50.930
God has spoken, but now you're doubting.

22:50.990 --> 22:52.972
If he's spoken, you say, no, I'm just trying to figure it out.

22:53.212 --> 22:54.093
You don't have to figure it out.

